component.name: LogAttribute

relationships.name: success
relationships.description: All FlowFiles are routed to this relationship

Log Level.name: Log Level
Log Level.description: The Log Level to use when logging the Attributes

Log Payload.name: Log Payload
Log Payload.description: If true, the FlowFile's payload will be logged, in addition to its attributes; otherwise, just the Attributes will be logged.

Attributes to Log.name: Attributes to Log
Attributes to Log.description: A comma-separated list of Attributes to Log. If not specified, all attributes will be logged unless `Attributes to Log by Regular Expression` is modified. There's an AND relationship between the two properties.

attributes-to-log-regex.name: attributes-to-log-regex
attributes-to-log-regex.displayName: Attributes to Log by Regular Expression
attributes-to-log-regex.description: A regular expression indicating the Attributes to Log. If not specified, all attributes will be logged unless `Attributes to Log` is modified. There's an AND relationship between the two properties.

Attributes to Ignore.name: Attributes to Ignore
Attributes to Ignore.description: A comma-separated list of Attributes to ignore. If not specified, no attributes will be ignored unless `Attributes to Ignore by Regular Expression` is modified. There's an OR relationship between the two properties.

attributes-to-ignore-regex.name: attributes-to-ignore-regex
attributes-to-ignore-regex.displayName: Attributes to Ignore by Regular Expression
attributes-to-ignore-regex.description: A regular expression indicating the Attributes to Ignore. If not specified, no attributes will be ignored unless `Attributes to Ignore` is modified. There's an OR relationship between the two properties.

Log prefix.name: Log prefix
Log prefix.description: Log prefix appended to the log lines. It helps to distinguish the output of multiple LogAttribute processors.

character-set.name: character-set
character-set.description: The name of the CharacterSet to use

validationErrors: 'Relationship success' is invalid because Relationship 'success' is not connected to any component and is not auto-terminated

relationships.name: failure
relationships.description: SQL query execution failed. Incoming FlowFile will be penalized and routed to this relationship

relationships.name: nodata
relationships.description: Successful but no new data to process.

Questionari connessione dati.name: Questionari connessione dati
Questionari connessione dati.description: The database containing records of questionari

Tabella db.name: Tabella db
Tabella db.description: Name of table including schema (if applicable)

Query per caricare questionari.name: Query per caricare questionari
Query per caricare questionari.description: Field names (in order) to read from the source table. ie. the select fields. The format is separated by newline. Inconsistent order will cause corruption of the downstream Hive data.

Mapping.name: Mapping
Mapping.description: Choose type of mapping to JSON

Load Strategy.name: Load Strategy
Load Strategy.description: Whether to load the entire table or perform an incremental extract

Date Field.name: Date Field
Date Field.description: Source field containing a modified date for tracking incremental load

Overlap Period.name: Overlap Period
Overlap Period.description: Amount of time to overlap into the last load date to ensure long running transactions missed by previous load weren't missed. Recommended: >0s

Max Wait Time.name: Max Wait Time
Max Wait Time.description: The maximum amount of time allowed for a running SQL select query  , zero means there is no limit. Max time less than 1 second will be equal to zero.

Backoff Period.name: Backoff Period
Backoff Period.description: Only records older than the backoff period will be eligible for pickup. This can be used in the ILM use case to define a retention period. Recommended: >5m

relationships.name: failure
relationships.description: Files that could not be written to the output directory for some reason are transferred to this relationship

relationships.name: success
relationships.description: Files that have been successfully written to the output directory are transferred to this relationship

Directory.name: Directory
Directory.description: The directory to which files should be written. You may use expression language such as /aa/bb/${path}

Conflict Resolution Strategy.name: Conflict Resolution Strategy
Conflict Resolution Strategy.description: Indicates what should happen when a file with the same name already exists in the output directory

Create Missing Directories.name: Create Missing Directories
Create Missing Directories.description: If true, then missing destination directories will be created. If false, flowfiles are penalized and sent to failure.

Maximum File Count.name: Maximum File Count
Maximum File Count.description: Specifies the maximum number of files that can exist in the output directory

Last Modified Time.name: Last Modified Time
Last Modified Time.description: Sets the lastModifiedTime on the output file to the value of this attribute.  Format must be yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ssZ.  You may also use expression language such as ${file.lastModifiedTime}.

Permissions.name: Permissions
Permissions.description: Sets the permissions on the output file to the value of this attribute.  Format must be either UNIX rwxrwxrwx with a - in place of denied permissions (e.g. rw-r--r--) or an octal number (e.g. 644).  You may also use expression language such as ${file.permissions}.

Owner.name: Owner
Owner.description: Sets the owner on the output file to the value of this attribute.  You may also use expression language such as ${file.owner}.

Group.name: Group
Group.description: Sets the group on the output file to the value of this attribute.  You may also use expression language such as ${file.group}.
